THE PROBLEM
Given J sets of hybrid data, each formed by I1, I2, . . . , I J individuals, respectively, the same model can be fitted to each one. The J populations can be represented, according to Eq. (6), by different vectors of parameters:
√∞M1, A11, 11, . . . , A1C, 1C√û ... √∞M J , A1J , 1J , . . . , ACJ , CJ √û
In each model there are 2C √æ 1 parameters, C being the number of frequencies used. The problem is to know if there is any difference among the parameters (or set
of parameters) from the different populations. The next Null Hypotheses (NHs) are of interest:
